// <li>Phase 2 is tag-dependent</li>
// </ul>
//<br></br>
// Phase 2 for `string...` converts `expressions` to `strings` and concatenates. `base16` and `base64`
// tags do not allow `expressions`.

// Simple types: <br>/<br>
// Always plain data. Includes `nil`, `boolean`, `int`, `float`, `decimal`. <br>/<br>
// Sequence: <br>/<br>
// Always plain data. Includes `string`, `xml`. <br>/<br>
// Structural: <br>/<br>
// Plain data if members are `array`/`tuple`, `map`/`record`, `table`. <br>/<br>
// Behavioural: <br>/<br>
// Not plain data. Includes `function`, `object`, `error`, `stream`, `typedesc`, `handle`.

